    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-and-lemon-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While your pasta is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-and-lemon-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to brown and crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-and-lemon-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, roughly chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-and-lemon-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>zingy dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and add<strong> </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>zingy dressing </strong>and give it a gentle mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>zingy salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-and-lemon-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>chorizo has crisped, reduce the heat to medium and add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, and your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>drained pasta </strong>with a few splashes of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-and-lemon-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>clotted cream </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully combined</p><p>Tip: Add more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p><p>Squeeze in the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>chorizo & lemon pasta</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-and-lemon-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chorizo & lemon linguine </strong>topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>zingy salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and garnish with a<strong> lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
